> Mondale </PERSON>, following victories over <PERSON> Mondale </PERSON> in the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> primary and <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION> caucuses. One year ago: The board of trustees at <ORGANIZATION> Gallaudet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, the world's only liberal arts college for the deaf, chose a hearing woman, <PERSON> Elisabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Zinser </PERSON>, school president over two deaf candidates. Outraged students shut down the campus, forcing <PERSON> Zinser </PERSON>'s ouster and the selection of a deaf president in her place. Today's Birthdays: TV personality <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> McMahon </PERSON> is 66. Conductor <PERSON> Sarah </PERSON> <PERSON> Caldwell </PERSON> is 65. <ORGANIZATION> CIA </ORGANIZATION> director <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Webster </PERSON> is 65. The chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Greenspan </PERSON>, is 63. The first woman in space, Soviet cosmonaut <PERSON> Valentina </PERSON> <PERSON> Tereshkova </PERSON>, is 52. Actor <PERSON> Ben </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> is 47. Opera singer <PERSON> Dame </PERSON> <PERSON> Kiri </PERSON> <PERSON> Te </PERSON> <PERSON> Kanawa </PERSON> is 45. Actor-director <PERSON> Rob </PERSON> <PERSON> Reiner </PERSON> is 42. Thought for Today: `` Caveat actor.'' Let the doer beware. _ Latin proverb.
