for <PERSON> Matheny </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Correction </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Vaughn </PERSON> <PERSON> Overstreet </PERSON> said he would not identify the workers because they had not yet been notified. The governor said former <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Virginia </PERSON> <PERSON> Dill </PERSON> <PERSON> McCarty </PERSON> would head a <ORGANIZATION> Correction </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> internal investigation. A report is due Friday. <PERSON> Bayh </PERSON> said earlier he thought that proper procedure was for a victim to be notified that his or her attacker was being released. But <PERSON> Christopher </PERSON> <PERSON> Meloy </PERSON>, supervisor of work release services for the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Correction </ORGANIZATION>, said policy calls for victims such as <PERSON> Bianco </PERSON> to be notified of a release only if they had previously requested such notification. <PERSON> Meloy </PERSON> did not know if <PERSON> Bianco </PERSON> had made such a request. `` Some victims are not that concerned about it, some victims move and are very difficult to get in touch with, and sometimes we do n't even have an easily identifiable victim,'' he said <PERSON> Meloy </PERSON> also defended the programs. `` We for the most part have been enjoying a successful track record,'' <PERSON> Meloy </PERSON> said. Succeeding in either program means the offender has not been returned to the institution after his full release, <PERSON> Meloy </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Bayh </PERSON> spokesman <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Nation </PERSON> said no inmates involved in the special assignment program will receive a pass for the next four weeks while the policy is reviewed. <PERSON> Bayh </PERSON> said the review would determine whether the program `` deserves to be continued or whether we should eliminate it entirely.'' <PERSON> Matheney </PERSON> got the pass under a program that sends inmates at state expense to work for <ORGANIZATION> Interfaith </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Housing </ORGANIZATION>, a not-for-profit organization that refurbishes hoouses and sells them to low - and middle-income families, <PERSON> Meloy </PERSON> said <PERSON> Bayh </PERSON> said he was aware of <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION>'s Regulated Community Assignment program and work-release program, but he was unaware of the special release program that allowed <PERSON> Matheney </PERSON> an eight-hour pass. `` In fact, I have some serious doubts about this program because it does not help significantly with the overcrowding situtation in the prison. It is not related to work-release activities which prepare inmates for meeting full employment in the private sector. `` This is used, as I understand it, as a tool to promote good behavior in the prison walls. And it seems to me that there may be some other less risky methods to make that possible,'' <PERSON> Bayh </PERSON> said.
