 `` Money for Nothing'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- _ Dire Straits This greatest-hits collection, coming as it does in the midst of <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Knopfler </PERSON>'s public nonchalance about the future of Dire Straits, if any, has an air of finality to it. But this is no `` Crossroads'' - style retrospective; rather, it's the obligatory, single-disc collection with the obligatory live track `` not previously available'' _ in this case, the gentle `` Portobello Belle Much of the material is, then, Dire Straits' `` hits.'' But the band has had few real hit singles; they are an album group, and most fans will already have many of these songs. One notable omission is `` Skateaway'' from `` Making Movies,'' which became a semi-video-hit in the early days of <ORGANIZATION> MTV </ORGANIZATION>. `` Money for Nothing'' _ this album, not the single, which is indeed included _ also has one major fault: an unfortunate remixing of the fine dance track, `` Twisting by the Pool.'' This time, the sound is thinner, and some of <PERSON> Knopfler </PERSON>'s vocals _ about the closest his singing ever came to a rock' n' roll rave-up _ have actually been deleted. Still, many of these songs remain certifiably brilliant. <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Knopfler </PERSON> was fond of introducing his group in concert as the `` Dire Straits rock' n' roll band,'' and it has been that milieu, not his session work or his film scores, that stands as his highest testament. _ By <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Byrd </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
