s depression with hypnosis, repeating _ as <PERSON> Racn </PERSON> to write your concerto. ... you will work with great facility. ... the concerto will be of an excellent quality.''' He did. He did. It is. <PERSON> Kissin </PERSON>'s performance is excellent but not hypnotic. It's nice to see the infrequently recorded Etudes-Tableaux coupled with the concerto. They have a Chopinesque flavor to them, varying in moods. <PERSON> Kissin </PERSON> is more successful in the more intimate, quieter moments. By the way, why include only six of the nine etudes in Op. 39? At only 59:53, the disc has plenty of room to include the other three. _ By <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Wakin </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
