<HEAD>Dollar, Stocks Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar edged lower against the Japanese yen and share prices also fell on the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> today. The dollar started the week at 127.55 yen, down 0.57 yen from Friday's 128.12-yen close. It closed at 127.63 yen after ranging between 127.50 yen and 127.68 yen. It had edged up 2.12 yen over four trading days last week. `` The market wanted to test the dollar's lower depths, but commercial buying orders were too strong,'' said <PERSON> Kaneo </PERSON> <PERSON> Ogino </PERSON>, a dealer with <ORGANIZATION> Goldman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sachs </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>. `` The dollar is still mildly bearish and will move in a tight range for the time being,'' he added. Dealers said market activity wavered without strong direction and people were taking a `` wait-and-see'' attitude because of concern over possible Japanese interest rates hikes. `` This week, people are waiting for a conference Wednesday by <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> Governor <PERSON> Satoshi </PERSON> <PERSON> Sumita </PERSON> and the release of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> unemployment figures due out Friday,'' said one dealer with a major Japanese securities firm. On the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Nikkei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Average </ORGANIZATION> of 225 selected issues, a 73.63-point loser last week, shed another 123.24 points, or 0.38 percent, today to close at 31,876.86. Investors moved to the sidelines ahead of the settlement of March futures contracts scheduled for Tuesday, dealers said. `` They are also watching the monetary stance of the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGA