 An `` overlap of functions'' since <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> was acquired by <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Metropolitan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> has contributed to a decision to lay off 550 of the company's 2,350 employees in its <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION> headquarters, officials announced today. The layoffs, amounting to about 23.4 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION> staff, are to take place over the next several weeks, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> said The company will be left with about 1,800 employees in <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION> and 100,000 worldwide. `` The decision to eliminate these positions was necessary to make <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> a stronger, more profitable company, prepared to compete successfully in the world marketplace,'' <PERSON> Ian </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Martin </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer of <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> and head of Grand Metropolitan's worldwide foods group, said in a statement. `` We have concluded that the <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> business has been operating at a competitive disadvantage which must be corrected. Additionally, the merger of Grand Met and <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> created some overlap of functions which will be eliminated,'' he said. After a three-month fight, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> in December agreed to accept a sweetened $ 5.68 billion takeover offer from the Britain-based Grand Metropolitan. Grand Met reported sales of more than $ 11 billion in fiscal 1988. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> had sales of $ 6.2 billion.
