<HEAD>Cost of Living Very Well up 8.7 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The cost of living outrageously well leapt 8.7 percent in 1988, and <LOCATION> Petrossian </LOCATION> beluga caviar led the way with an increase of more than 41 percent, according to survey released Monday. A survey commissioned by <ORGANIZATION> Moet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Chandon </ORGANIZATION> champagne tracked the cost of a dozen luxury items and services in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, and found they went up in price at twice the 4.4 percent rate of the government's Consumer Price Index. A round-trip ticket on the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> France </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Concorde </ORGANIZATION> from <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> cost $ 4,876, up 10.2 percent from $ 4,424 in 1987. A <ORGANIZATION> Rolls-Royce </ORGANIZATION> Corniche convertible cost $ 205,500, up 12 percent from $ 183,500; the caviar cost $ 47, up from $ 33.25; a bottle of <PERSON> Hennessy </PERSON> X.O. cognac cost $ 78.95, up 7 percent from $ 73.79, while a bottle of <PERSON> Dom </PERSON> <PERSON> Perignon </PERSON> cost $ 69.97, up 8.5 percent from $ 64.50; and a men's Rolex Oyster perpetual day-date watch with President bracelet could be had for $ 11,700, 12 percent more than last year's $ 10,450 Some items registered price increases that were near or lower than the overall CPI increase: a ticket to `` Cats,'' $ 50, up 5.3 percent from last year's $ 47.50; a wash, cut and blow dry in one of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s more exclusive salons cost $ 70, up 4.5 percent from $ 67; and a full-length mink, $ 17,000, up $ 500 or 3 percent from last year's $ 16,500. The prics of three items remained unchanged: a one-hour limousine rental at $ 40, a pound of imported chocolate truffles at $ 36, and maid service for a day, at $ 88.
