<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, acquired by <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Metropolitan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> for $ 5.68 billion two months ago, announced plans Monday to lay off 550 of the company's 2,350 employees in its <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION> headquarters. An `` overlap of functions'' since the food and restaurant company was acquired by <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Met </ORGANIZATION> was cited as a reason for the across-the-board layoffs, and one analyst expressed surprise about the amount of fat on the Doughboy. `` These guys -LRB- Grand Met -RRB- are obviously looking to become low-cost producers,'' said <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Carver </PERSON>, an analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Dain </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bosworth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. The layoffs over the next several weeks will leave <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> with about 1,800 employees in <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION> and 100,000 worldwide. `` The decision to eliminate these positions was necessary to make <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> a stronger, more profitable company, prepared to compete successfully in the world marketplace,'' <PERSON> Ian </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Martin </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer of <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> and head of Grand Metropolitan's worldwide foods group, said in a statement. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Haeg </PERSON> said the layoffs affect all job classifications, from clerical support employees to managerial and staff-level functions. Last month, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> announced the closing of two plants, in <LOCATION> Grand </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Forks </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.D. </LOCATION>, and <PERSON> Joplin </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Mo. </LOCATION>, which will result in 334 layoffs. The shutdowns, effective the end of March, are because of surplus production capacity resulting from acquisitions and were in the works before the takeover. After a three-month fight, <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> in December agreed to accept a sweetened $ 5.68 billion takeover offer from Grand Metropolitan. The acquisition was completed in January. Grand Met is a British real estate, liquor and gambling conglomerate. Its <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> holdings include <PERSON> Alpo </PERSON> dog food and Pearle Vision Centers. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> makes <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> flour, <ORGANIZATION> Green </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Giant </ORGANIZATION> vegetables, <PERSON> Haagen </PERSON> <PERSON> Dazs </PERSON> ice cream and a variety of other products. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> also owns the Burger King, <PERSON> Bennigan </PERSON>'s and <ORGANIZATION> Steak </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Ale restaurant chains. Grand Met reported sales of more than $ 11 billion in fiscal 1988. <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> had sales of $ 6.2 billion.
